# Workspace the server may read/write (defaults to current working directory if unset)
WOP_WORKSPACE=/absolute/path/to/your/project

# Way of Pi data directory (default ~/.wayofpi). Tunnel login (Settings → ngrok → section 4) writes tunnel-gate.v1.json here; Vite dev + Bun both read it.
# WOP_HOME=/path/to/your/wayofpi-data

# Optional comma-separated substrings: if the request Host (or X-Forwarded-Host) contains any of these (case-insensitive), tunnel login applies when enabled — in addition to hostnames containing "ngrok".
# WOP_TUNNEL_GATE_HOST_MARKERS=trycloudflare.com

# Claw `.claw/` folder: absolute path to Way of Pi checkout root (parent of `.claw/`). Not the same as WOP_WORKSPACE.
# Default: inferred from server file layout. See docs/WOP_NAMESPACE.md (WOP_CLAW_HOST_ROOT).
# WOP_CLAW_HOST_ROOT=/absolute/path/to/wayofpi

# Claw schedules: when 1/true/on, Bun runs cron/once schedules from host `.claw/schedule/` via headless Pi (needs WOP_CHAT_ENGINE=auto or pi with pi on PATH). See docs/WOP_CLAW_MODE_PLAN.md.
# WOP_CLAW_SCHEDULER=1
# Claw chat uses the same engine as Simple/Technical. When WOP_CHAT_ENGINE is unset, the server defaults to auto (headless Pi when `pi` resolves). Set bundled or bun to force Bun-only. For strict Pi, use pi.

# Claw inbound webhook: set to 0/false/off to reject POST /api/claw/inbound even if a secret file exists under `.wayofpi/`.
# WOP_CLAW_INBOUND=0

# API + WebSocket port
WOP_SERVER_PORT=3333

# Electron dev (`ELECTRON_DEV=1`): when unset, Electron auto-starts the Bun API (`bun run server/index.ts`) before the window if `/api/health` is not already current. Set to 1/true/yes/on to skip autostart (you run Bun yourself).
# WOP_ELECTRON_SKIP_BUN_AUTOSTART=1

# Settings → Restart server… → POST /api/server/restart exits this Bun process. In dev (NODE_ENV≠production) this is ON when unset. In production, set to 1/true/yes/on to allow. Set 0/false/no/off to disable in dev. Restart npm run dev yourself after exit.
# WOP_ALLOW_SERVER_RESTART=0

# Optional: absolute path to ngrok CLI (overrides PATH and bundled `node_modules/ngrok/bin` when optionalDependency ngrok is installed). Leading ~/ is expanded. Entire ngrok stack is optional — omit `ngrok` from installs with npm install --omit=optional in apps/wayofwork-ui if you never use tunnels.
# WOP_NGROK_BINARY=/path/to/ngrok

# Settings → ngrok: when 0/false/no/off, Way of Pi does not spawn or stop managed `ngrok http` from the UI (section 3). Saving the dashboard authtoken (section 2), install-bundled, tunnel-gate, and LAN/public hints still work; unset = spawn allowed.
# WOP_ALLOW_NGROK_SPAWN=0

# Optional: ngrok agent local web UI (inspector API). Default 127.0.0.1:4040. Set if your ngrok.yml uses a custom web_addr so Way of Pi can read /api/tunnels and pass --web-addr when starting the managed tunnel.
# WOP_NGROK_WEB_ADDR=127.0.0.1:4040

# LLM: ollama (default) or openrouter
WOP_LLM_PROVIDER=ollama

# Cap in-memory + JSONL transcript before each model request (Bun path and Pi JSON prompt size). 0 / false / no / off = disable. See docs/WOP_PI_TOKEN_CONTEXT_DISCIPLINE.md (repo enforcement).
# WOP_CHAT_CONTEXT_BUDGET=1
# Max non-system messages and ~chars in the tail after trim (defaults 120 and 120000).
# WOP_CHAT_MAX_MESSAGES=120
# WOP_CHAT_MAX_INPUT_CHARS=120000

# Chat engine: omit = auto (Pi JSON when `pi` resolves, else Bun → WOP_LLM_PROVIDER). Do NOT set WOP_CHAT_ENGINE=ollama — use WOP_LLM_PROVIDER for ollama vs openrouter. Only bundled/bun forces Bun-only; any other typo/non-keyword is treated like auto.
# WOP_CHAT_ENGINE=auto
# WOP_CHAT_ENGINE=pi
# WOP_CHAT_ENGINE=bundled
# Absolute path to the Pi CLI if not on PATH (leading ~/ is expanded to your home directory).
# Resolution order: WOP_PI_BINARY (existing file) → PATH (Bun.which) → repo scripts/wop-headless-pi (POSIX: sources
# playground .env then exec pi — same env idea as ppi/just pi, cwd stays workspace) → ~/.local/bin/pi, …
# Electron dev spawn prepends the same PATH extras as start-wayofwork-ui.sh.
# WOP_PI_BINARY=/path/to/pi
# WOP_PI_BINARY=~/.local/bin/pi
# Kill `pi` if JSON lines stop for this many ms (default 900000). Min 30000, max 3600000.
# WOP_PI_JSON_TIMEOUT_MS=900000

# All workspace chat personas: Pi-shaped LLM tools read / list_dir / grep / write (+ optional bash). Set to 0/false/no/off to disable.
# WOP_ORCHESTRATOR_TOOLS=1
# Host shell for orchestrator `bash` tool only (trusted workspace). Default off.
# Orchestrator bash tool: on by default with orchestrator tools. Set to 0/false/no/off to disable.
# WOP_ORCHESTRATOR_BASH=0

# Orchestrator git_* tools: status/remote/fetch/pull/push plus branches/checkout/merge/add/commit (default on with WOP_ORCHESTRATOR_TOOLS). Set to 0/false/no/off to hide.
# WOP_ORCHESTRATOR_GIT_TOOLS=1

# Ollama (OpenAI-compatible). Same repo `.env` as Pi: **`OLLAMA_BASE_URL`** is accepted too (e.g. http://localhost:11434); **`OLLAMA_HOST`** wins if both are set.
OLLAMA_HOST=http://127.0.0.1:11434
# OLLAMA_BASE_URL=http://localhost:11434
# Default model: **`OLLAMA_MODEL`** overrides **`agent/settings.json`** `defaultModel` when unset (Pi-style).
OLLAMA_MODEL=llama3

# Optional: exact context window (tokens) for the status bar `%` meter when the provider does not report it; overrides heuristics from the model id.
# WOP_MODEL_CONTEXT_TOKENS=8192

# OpenRouter (set WOP_LLM_PROVIDER=openrouter)
# OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-...
# OPENROUTER_MODEL=openrouter/auto

# Optional system prompt injected on each WebSocket session
# WOP_SYSTEM_PROMPT=You are a helpful coding assistant.

# Real interactive terminal (WebSocket /ws/terminal). Host shell, cwd = workspace — trusted machines only.
# Dev server defaults this ON when unset (and `npm run dev` forces NODE_ENV=development for Bun so inherited production does not skip that default). Set to 0, false, no, or off to disable. Production: use 1 / true / yes / on to enable the host PTY.
WOP_ALLOW_TERMINAL=1

# Optional: override default shell (Unix). Default is /bin/bash; on Windows cmd.exe is used.
# WOP_SHELL=/bin/zsh
